Ext.data.JsonP['Installing_the_Android_NDK']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Installing the Android NDK</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-31524316\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Installing the Android NDK</h1>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524316_InstallingtheAndroidNDK-Contents\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Contents</span></h2>\n    <p>    </p>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Installing_the_Android_NDK-section-src-31524316_InstallingtheAndroidNDK-CompatibilityandDownload\">Compatibility and Download</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Installing_the_Android_NDK-section-src-31524316_InstallingtheAndroidNDK-Installation\">Installation</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524316_InstallingtheAndroidNDK-CompatibilityandDownload\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Compatibility and Download</span></h2>\n    <p>The Android NDK is required to build native modules for Android, or to build the Titanium SDK from source.    </p>\n    <p>The NDK is <strong class=\" \">not</strong> required to build, run, or distribute apps using the Titanium SDK.    </p>\n    <p>Titanium supports NDK Revision 12.    </p>\n    <p>Download the appropriate NDK archive from the following site:    </p>\n    <p>    <img src=\"images/download/attachments/29004836/download_05.png\" alt=\"images/download/attachments/29004836/download_05.png\" class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"64\">\n        </img></p>\n    <p><a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"http://developer.android.com/sdk/ndk/index.html\" target=\"_blank\">Download the Android NDK on developer.android.com</a>    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-31524316_InstallingtheAndroidNDK-Installation\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Installation</span></h2>\n    <p>To install the Android NDK, simply expand the archive in the folder where you want to install it.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox admonition admonition-warning aui-message problem shadowed information-macro\">\n            <p>The path to the NDK must not contain spaces or special characters, such as a dollar sign, ampersand, etc.    </p>\n    </div>\n        <p>After installing the NDK, define an environment variable identifying the path to the NDK. For example,<br>on OS X, you might add the following to your <tt class=\" \">.bash_profile</tt>:    </br></p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">export ANDROID_NDK=~/android-ndk-r9d </code><code class=\"comments\">//path to your NDK</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=31524316\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Installing the Android NDK"});